00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:01,975
Freedom...

559
00:53:03,834 --> 00:53:09,910
Gandhi won it for India...
not the gun.

560
00:53:11,034 --> 00:53:14,982
The gun only knows how to avenge...

561
00:53:16,367 --> 00:53:17,869
Commander...

562
00:53:18,300 --> 00:53:23,113
revenge does not set you free..

563
00:53:23,167 --> 00:53:28,139
True freedom lies beyond violence..

564
00:53:30,334 --> 00:53:36,285
Remember...
Revenge only begets revenge.

565
00:53:42,900 --> 00:53:46,507
- Don't you understand?
Can't you hear me?

566
00:53:47,867 --> 00:53:49,540
I am not going anywhere.

567
00:53:49,800 --> 00:53:51,302
I am staying here.

568
00:53:55,167 --> 00:53:57,044
With my father.

569
00:54:09,734 --> 00:54:11,372
Jahid.. to the left...

570
00:54:22,167 --> 00:54:23,271
What is it now?

571
00:54:23,367 --> 00:54:25,404
I ask you, one last time...

572
00:54:26,734 --> 00:54:29,180
Will you go or not?

573
00:54:29,367 --> 00:54:30,778
Should I write it down for you?

574
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:32,040
I will not!

575
00:54:35,300 --> 00:54:36,472
What is this, mother?!

576
00:54:37,234 --> 00:54:38,110
Will you go or not?

577
00:54:38,233 --> 00:54:40,509
Please hear me out...

578
00:54:40,767 --> 00:54:41,268
- Will you go or not?

579
00:54:41,334 --> 00:54:42,438
Put the gun down mother...

580
00:54:42,500 --> 00:54:44,104
Will you go or notl?

581
00:54:46,333 --> 00:54:47,403
Mother, please...

582
00:54:56,767 --> 00:54:59,043
Would you really have
shot yourself that day?

583
00:55:00,900 --> 00:55:02,379
Do you doubt me?

584
00:55:04,167 --> 00:55:06,113
No. I'm sure.

585
00:55:07,667 --> 00:55:09,374
You wouldn't have.

586
00:55:15,267 --> 00:55:18,908
Was there any other reason
for me to live... besides you?

587
00:55:23,800 --> 00:55:25,336
Or is there?

588
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:32,972
I bore those long
painful years for you...

589
00:55:33,200 --> 00:55:37,080
Don't...There you go again...

590
00:55:37,134 --> 00:55:38,875
You have to listen to me.

591
00:55:41,934 --> 00:55:44,972
Your father never really
cared for me. Our marriage was dead.

592
00:55:46,900 --> 00:55:49,278
Which is why he gambled his life...

593
00:55:49,767 --> 00:55:51,075
our home...

594
00:55:51,833 --> 00:55:53,813
our honor...

595
00:55:53,867 --> 00:55:57,371
your future... risked it all.

596
00:56:00,300 --> 00:56:07,115
Do we have to see everything
through your eyes?

597
00:56:08,367 --> 00:56:09,641
Always?

598
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:15,878
There are other ways of seeing.
Try sometime...

599
00:56:23,667 --> 00:56:27,137
Either way,
you will always blame me...

600
00:56:30,267 --> 00:56:34,272
I am used to it.

601
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:44,107
I know you love your father
more than anyone else...

602
00:56:47,767 --> 00:56:49,940
You certainly don't realise...

603
00:56:51,667 --> 00:56:54,341
What I went through
when you were away.

604
00:56:55,833 --> 00:57:01,681
Hilaal had lost himself in
the hospital, a saint saving lives.

605
00:57:04,100 --> 00:57:09,948
I used to wail like a
hollow bamboo in your memory.

606
00:57:15,033 --> 00:57:19,709
I would wait months for you
to return home in the holidays.

607
00:57:23,634 --> 00:57:29,710
It is my fate to long... to wait...

608
00:57:36,267 --> 00:57:38,213
First for you...

609
00:57:41,634 --> 00:57:42,305
Now...

610
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:46,772
And now?

611
00:57:49,734 --> 00:57:55,844
The wives of disappeared people
are called 'half-widows' here.

612
00:57:59,667 --> 00:58:01,647
We can only wait.

613
00:58:06,833 --> 00:58:09,040
That is all I can do.

614
00:58:13,800 --> 00:58:14,870
Wait.

615
00:58:16,067 --> 00:58:17,569
For father to return?

616
00:58:19,534 --> 00:58:20,478
Yes.

617
00:58:23,967 --> 00:58:26,538
Or for his corpse.

618
00:58:32,634 --> 00:58:34,204
My father is alive!

619
00:58:35,934 --> 00:58:37,038
He's alive!

620
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:39,840
Do you understand?!

621
00:58:42,167 --> 00:58:45,979
Please tell me mother, he's alive...

622
00:58:48,667 --> 00:58:50,203
He's alive!

623
00:58:59,167 --> 00:59:01,147
Tell me mother...

624
00:59:03,667 --> 00:59:05,169
he's alive...

625
00:59:06,967 --> 00:59:08,674
Please tell me...

626
00:59:17,934 --> 00:59:19,607
Elections are the first step...

627
00:59:19,667 --> 00:59:20,702
on the long road to peace...

628
00:59:20,767 --> 00:59:23,680
It is a difficult journey...
but we can see our destination...

629
00:59:23,734 --> 00:59:26,408
Wherever you come from...

630
00:59:26,467 --> 00:59:27,969
people want the same thing...

631
00:59:28,133 --> 00:59:31,137
Our schools have been turned
into Army camps...

632
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:33,539
It is not a democracy...

633
00:59:34,400 --> 00:59:37,745
it a suffocating system.
A 'suffo-cracy'!

634
00:59:41,434 --> 00:59:45,610
The town squares are lined with bunkers
and streets with barbed wires.

635
00:59:45,667 --> 00:59:47,442
According to the APDP there are...

636
00:59:47,500 --> 00:59:50,037
over eight thousand people
who are missing since arrest...

637
00:59:56,500 --> 00:59:57,843
- Your numbers are wrong...

638
00:59:57,900 --> 01:00:00,779
What about those three hundred
thousand Kashmiri Pandits...

639
01:00:00,834 --> 01:00:03,542
displaced from their homes,
living as refugees...

640
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:05,170
Will you not count them
amongst the disappeared?

641
01:00:05,400 --> 01:00:08,904
My brother disappeared months back.

642
01:00:08,934 --> 01:00:12,575
We have to raise our voices
to search for our own.

643
01:00:12,634 --> 01:00:14,443
- What do we want?
- Freedom...

644
01:00:14,500 --> 01:00:16,104
- We'll snatch away...
- Freedom...

645
01:00:16,167 --> 01:00:18,977
And for this I am
running for elections...

646
01:00:25,134 --> 01:00:29,480
I would like to remind you
of our neighbor that arms and trains...

647
01:00:29,534 --> 01:00:33,573
misguided Kashmiri youth
to kill innocent people...

648
01:00:33,800 --> 01:00:39,716
In 1948, they had looted Kashmiri's
when they came as tribals...

649
